Tens of thousands of protestors marched through central Paris yesterday, angry at the French government legalisation of same sex marriage.

The historic Esplanade des Invalides in the 7th arrondissement was a sea of protesters waving trademark pink and blue flags.

As night fell, several hundred protesters clashed with police, throwing bottles and chasing journalists.

