Interior Minister Manuel Valls mobilised 4,500 officers to police the event.

The situation escalated Tuesday when far-right writer Dominique Venner, who is linked to a far-right French nationalist party, shot and killed himself inside Paris’ Notre Dame Cathedral. He had called for 'spectacular' action to protect France’s identity, and was denouncing same-sex marriage law.

Hollande’s Socialist Party denounced the protest, highlighting the fact that the law has already passed in parliament and was validated by the Constitutional Council.

The conservative opposition UMP party was split over whether to continue the rallies.

